{
  "doc_id": "22787",
  "text": "Transcription factors of N-MYC and C-MYC were previously shown to contribute to tumourigenesis and progression in NB [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . LAN-1, NB-19, and SK-N-DZ were reported high N-MYC expression [CITATION_3] . MYC activity is usually regulated by GSK3β. In our study, expressions of N-MYC and C-MYC did not show solid relationship between pS9-GSK3β and MK-2206 resistance ( Figs. 5, 6 ).",
